{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771596570,"nonce":"jwPkgAGLWykE/8La2J7m+qbOojQ=","title":"Missing database unique index on borrower student_id","message":"The Borrower model validates uniqueness of student_id at the application level (line 13):\n\n  validates :student_id, uniqueness: true, if: Proc.new{|u| u.student? \u0026\u0026 u.student_id.present? }\n\nBut there is no corresponding unique index in the database. The schema only has a plain column:\n\n  t.string \"student_id\"\n\nWithout a DB-level unique index, concurrent requests can bypass the Rails validation and insert duplicate student IDs. This needs a migration to add a conditional unique index (only for non-null values, since employees have nil student_id).\n\nSomething like:\n  add_index :borrowers, :student_id, unique: true, where: 'student_id IS NOT NULL'","files":null}]}